## ğŸ§  Why Use Backticks?

If you do:

A=hostname

then `$A` becomes "hostname" â€” just plain text.

But if you do:

A=hostname

then `$A` becomes something like "my-linux-vm" â€” the actual hostname.

âœ… Use backticks or `$(...)` to store command output in variables.

---

## ğŸ” Using Multiple `read` Inputs

We can collect more than one piece of information.

server_name=hostname
echo "Hello, my server name is $server_name"
echo
echo "What is your name?"
read B
echo
echo "What is your profession?"
read C
echo
echo "What is your favorite show?"
read D
echo
echo "Hello $B, your profession, $C, is awesome."
echo "$D is a good show."


